This paper discusses privacy concerns in data analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves using user personality to detect privacy concerns, which could also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for personalized privacy protection, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and databases (cs.DB).
